The 'Repeat' mechanism adds the risk of infinite loops in the code - the current parser was designed to guarantee eventual completion. Vendor output often changes in subtle ways and we did not want a minor change to cause an infinite loop - reliability is of utmost importance in our systems that use this code.

The existing code can deal with this - see this adaptation to your template with the following construct - a little bit of repetition but it will complete:

```
Start
  ^${lspid}[*\s]+${lsp_seq_num}\s+${lsp_checksum}\s+${lsp_holdtime}\s+${att}/${p}/${ol}
  ^\s+Hostname:\s+${hostname}
  ^\s+IP Address:\s+${ipv4_address}
  ^\s+IPv6 Address:\s+${ipv6_address}
  ^\s+Router ID:\s+${router_id} -> Prefixes

Prefixes
  ^\s+${prefixes}
# Perform a Record on the row captured so far, and continue with the same line.
  ^\S+ -> Continue.Record
# Now capture the values for the current line in the new record then jump to Start for the next line.
  ^${lspid}[*\s]+${lsp_seq_num}\s+${lsp_checksum}\s+${lsp_holdtime}\s+${att}/${p}/${ol} -> Start
```

