pywb uses the WSGI standard `wsgi.url_scheme` variable to determine the scheme, so if that's set to `https`, it should work

 If you're deploying with nginx and uwsgi and having nginx handle ssl, this can be done by adding the `UWSGI_SCHEME $scheme` param, eg, if pywb is running in uwsgi on port :8081, a config might be as follows:

```
    location / {
        include uwsgi_params;

        uwsgi_param UWSGI_SCHEME $scheme;
        uwsgi_pass localhost:8081;
    }
```

Hope this helps, I'm not sure if this is sufficient for Kubernetes, but would be curious to know. Perhaps should also be added to the pywb docs.

